  "prompt": "What are some lesser known facts about PM Narendra Modi?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are some lesser-known facts about Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi:\n\n1. **Early Life and Background:**\n   - Modi was born on September 17, 1950, in Vadnagar, Gujarat. He comes from a humble background; his family sold tea at a railway station.\n\n2. **RSS Involvement:**\n   - Modi has been associated with the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS), a Hindu nationalist volunteer organization, from an early age. He formally joined the RSS at the age of 20.\n\n3. **Travel and Pilgrimage:**\n   - Before entering politics, Modi spent considerable time traveling across India, including a two-year stint at the Himalayas where he lived as a monk among sadhus.\n\n4. **Educational Background:**\n   - Modi holds a master's degree in political science from Gujarat University.\n\n5. **Environmental Campaigns:**\n   - As Chief Minister of Gujarat, Modi initiated several environmental campaigns, including the planting of millions of trees and the \"Narmada River Conservation Program.\"\n\n6. **Writer and Author:**\n   - Modi has authored several books, including \"Exam Warriors,\" which is aimed at students, providing academic and stress-management tips.\n\n7. **Photography Enthusiast:**\n   - Modi has a keen interest in photography. His photographs have been displayed in exhibitions and he also ran a small photography business during his early years.\n\n8. **Yoga and Spirituality:**\n   - Modi practices yoga regularly and has advocated for its adoption globally. He played a pivotal role in promoting International Yoga Day.\n\n9. **Fashion Sense:**\n   - Known for his distinct sartorial choices, Modi often sports traditional Indian attire with a modern twist. His personalized 'Modi Kurta' has become quite popular.\n\n10. **Tech-Savvy Leader:**\n    - Narendra Modi is known for his tech-savvy approach, utilizing social media extensively for communication and governance. He premiered a holographic 3D campaign during the 2014 elections.\n\n11. **International Recognition:**\n    - Modi has received various international accolades and awards, including the United Nations' Champions of the Earth Award in 2018 for policy leadership.\n\n12. **Personal Fitness:**\n    - Modi is known for his disciplined lifestyle, which includes early morning routines and maintaining a strict diet.\n\nThese facets reflect the multifaceted personality and interests of Narendra Modi beyond his political career.",
